<dl><dd><em>Also known as: 把字句 ("bǎ"zìjù), 把 construction, preposition 把, disposal construction&#160;and pre-transitive 把.</em></dd></dl>
<p>Once you've gotten the hang of the basic <a href="&quot;Ba&quot;_sentence" class="mw-redirect" title="&quot;Ba&quot; sentence"><b>把 (bǎ) sentence</b></a> pattern, you can start to use it in some more complex and abstract ways.
</p>
<div id="toc" class="toc"><input type="checkbox" role="button" id="toctogglecheckbox" class="toctogglecheckbox" style="display:none" /><div class="toctitle" lang="en" dir="ltr"><h2>Contents</h2><span class="toctogglespan"><label class="toctogglelabel" for="toctogglecheckbox"></label></span></div>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="Advanced_uses_of_&quot;ba&quot;#Using_.E6.8A.8A_with_.E7.BB.99"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">Using 把 with 给</span></a>
<ul>
<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-2"><a href="Advanced_uses_of_&quot;ba&quot;#Structure"><span class="tocnumber">1.1</span> <span class="toctext">Structure</span></a></li>
<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-3"><a href="Advanced_uses_of_&quot;ba&quot;#Examples"><span class="tocnumber">1.2</span> <span class="toctext">Examples</span></a></li>
</ul>
</li>
<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-4"><a href="Advanced_uses_of_&quot;ba&quot;#Using_.E5.BD.93.E4.BD.9C_and_.E7.9C.8B.E4.BD.9C"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Using 当作 and 看作</span></a>
<ul>
